==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jointworm
<hw>Joint"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The larva of a small, hymenopterous fly (<spn>Eurytoma
hordei</spn>), which is found in gall-like swellings on the stalks of
wheat, usually at or just above the first joint. In some parts of
America it does great damage to the crop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Joist</ent>⟦br⟧
